narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Definitely doable if you just learning Spanish. Just stay on top of your work and you can do well.
Yes! Take it with Oscar! He's the man.Plus, it's a nice break from other classes of p-sets or papers. You'll definitely learn Spanish if you take this.

Even though most people who take the course have to take it, I would still recommend it to fellow students. I am still amazed by how far I've progressed with Spanish after never having taken Spanish before, taking L1, and then taking L2. Spanish 120 is great at giving you a much higher level of Spanish ability even if it is not fluency. Having class everyday does get old, but the homework for Spanish 120 was not very heavy.
